
=Bio=

“Katharina Moebus is an interdisciplinary designer working at the crossroads of design, art, activism, research, and education based in Berlin with her family. Current research interests focus on the commons, (feminist) solidarity economies, civic participation and cultures of resilience within urban neighbourhoods. Since end of 2016, she is PhD candidate at Sheffield University’s School of Architecture with her research project: Economies of Commoning “(economiesofcommoning.net).

